EXTRACTED VALUE: The food was amaizing!! My fav dish was the buttermilk battered deep fried quail. -so good-
Although they completely failed the night of our visit, the chef offered a good faith response and a generous if not worthless offer.
Live Irish music is a real treat also!
That particular evening was not a true special occasion for us, but Collage made it so!
As you can imagine, this was a surprising and unpleasant experience, and one that I felt you should be aware of. Beware!
All of this, in conjunction with the pricey menu, lead me to feel a sinking feeling of disappointment on every visit.
I also admit, I failed to call the manager.
We will definitely go back the next time we go to Tahoe.
